Preparation of Ni-doped green CDs (CDs

   1-DMF-1 h

): 1 mmol oPD and 0.1 mmol NiCl2 6H2O were dispersed in 10 mL DMF. The solution was sonicated for 25 min until the mixture was completely dissolved. The mixed solution was then transferred to the reaction kettle in a poly(tetrafluoroethylene) (Teflon)-lined autoclave (25 mL). The autoclave was then stored in an oven at 180 °C for 1 h and cooled naturally to room temperature. The original solution was then filtered twice through a 0.22 μm filter membrane. Subsequently, the solution was dialyzed for 24 h by a dialysis bag with a molecular weight of 1000 Da in order to remove some unreacted reactants and other impurities. Finally, the dialyzed solution was treated by rotary evaporation, and the obtained sample was dissolved in a suitable solvent for subsequent characterization.

Preparation of Ni-doped willow green CDs (CDs

   2-MeOH-3 h

): The whole synthesis method was the same as that of CDs1-DMF-1 h, except that the reaction solvent and reaction time were different. And the reaction solvent and reaction time were methanol and 3 h, respectively.

Preparation of Ni-doped willow yellow CDs (CDs

   3-MeOH-13 h

): The whole synthesis method was the same as that of CDs2-MeOH-3 h, except that the reaction time was 13 h.

Preparation of Ni-doped yellow CDs (CDs

   4-DMF-5 h

): The whole synthesis method was the same as that of CDs1-DMF-1 h, except that the reaction time was 5 h.

Preparation of Ni-doped orange CDs (CDs

   5-DMF-20 h

): The whole synthesis method was the same as that of CDs1-DMF-1 h, except that the reaction time was 20 h.

Preparation of Ni-doped red CDs (CDs

   6-DMF-20 h 8

): 8 mmol oPD and 0.8 mmol NiCl2 6H2O were dispersed in 10 mL DMF. The other conditions were prepared in the same way as the CDs5-DMF-20 h.
